nal [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] and the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]]. He has also represented [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]s.
==Early and personal life== Born in [[Haan]],<ref name = "SW">{{soccerway|elias-kachunga/126639|accessdate=25 June 2016}}</ref> Kachunga has a Congolese father and a German mother.<ref name = "Bild">{{cite web|url=http://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/elias-kachunga/ingolstadt-schon-fuenfter-klub-41632550.bild.html|title=Kachunga (23) ist der Wechsel-König|date=4 July 2015|accessdate=25 June 2016|language=German|author=Thorsten Felske|publisher=Bild}}</ref>
==Club career== Kachunga spent his early career in Germany with [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], [[VfL Osnabrück]], [[Hertha BSC]] and [[SC Paderborn 07]].<ref name = "SW"/><ref>{{fussballdaten|id=kachungaelias}}</ref> Following Paderborn's relegation, he moved to [[FC Ingolstadt 04]] in June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.de/de/liga/news/elias-kachunga-wechselt-zum-fc-ingolstadt.jsp|title=KACHUNGA NACH INGOLSTADT|date=26 June 2015|accessdate=25 June 2016|language=German|publisher=Bundesliga}}</ref> He was the club's record signing, at a transfer fee of €1.7 million.<ref name = "Bild"/> He signed a season-long loan deal with an option to buy at the end with English [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36626665|title=Elias Kachunga: Huddersfield sign Ingolstadt striker on loan|date=24 June 2016|accessdate=25 June 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his debut for them on 6 August 2016, scoring the first goal in a 2–1 win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36929750</ref> On 22 March 2017, Huddersfield paid Ingolstadt £1.1 million to turn Kachunga's loan deal into a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Elias Kachunga: Huddersfield Town sign on-loan striker for £1.1m|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39352870|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=22 March 2017}}</ref>
In December 2017 he was ruled-out for 3 months due to injury.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42399490</ref>
==International career== He has represented Germany at [[Germany national youth football team|under-19]] and [[Germany national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.<ref name = "SW"/>
Kachunga debuted for the senior [[DR Congo national football team]] in a friendly 2–1 loss to [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]] on 26 March 2017.<ref>https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39338662</ref><ref>http://www.leopardsfoot.com/leopards-la-rdc-chute-2-1-en-amical-face-au-kenya/</ref>
